#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/async-cheap-condition-before-await.md savings=0%
M||tx|---
M||titl|Check Cheap Conditions Before Async Flags
M||impa|hi
M||impa|avoids unnecessary async work when a synchronous guard already fails
M||tags|async, await, feature-flags, short-circuit, conditional
M||tx|---
M|Chec|tx|When a branch uses `await` for a flag or remote value and also requires a **cheap synchronous** condition (local props, request metadata, already-loaded state), evaluate the cheap condition **first**. Otherwise you pay for the async call even when the compound condition can never be true.
M|Chec|tx|This is a specialization of [Defer Await Until Needed](./async-defer-await.md) for `flag && cheapCondition` style checks.
M|Chec|**In|**
M|Chec|tx|```ts
M|Chec|tx|const someFlag = await getFlag()
M|Chec|tx|if (someFlag && someCondition) {
M|Chec|tx|// ...
M|Chec|tx|}
M|Chec|tx|```
M|Chec|**Co|**
M|Chec|tx|```ts
M|Chec|tx|if (someCondition) {
M|Chec|tx|const someFlag = await getFlag()
M|Chec|tx|if (someFlag) {
M|Chec|tx|// ...
M|Chec|tx|}
M|Chec|tx|}
M|Chec|tx|```
M|Chec|This|skipping it when `someCondition` is false removes that cost on the cold path.
M|Chec|tx|Keep the original order if `someCondition` is expensive, depends on the flag, or you must run side effects in a fixed order.